This paper is about language modeling using recurrent neural networks, which is a topic in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses a method for compressing the size of the model parameters, which is a common problem in machine learning and can be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments on data sets, which could potentially relate to sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the data sets involve image captioning or other visual tasks.
